HEADWORD: Monology
<hw>Mo*nol"o*gy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/.]</ety>
<def>The habit of soliloquizing, or of monopolizing
conversation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It was not by an insolent usurpation that Coleridge persisted in
<qex>monology</qex> through his whole life.</q> <rj><qau>De
Quincey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

